"reviewcomment":"OMG, I am truly on &#34;cloud 9&#34; when I make it over from the Chelsea Market!  There are so many farm fresh, salads, and appetizer bar options! Not to mention Hemispheres has three main entree stations to choose from, that offer hot and unique dinning options for lunch and dinner. It&#39;s hard to name exact dishes since they change the menu every week, but in the past their fish/seafood is spot on, pork loins are tender, and their soul food side dishes are exactly that... food for the soul! Even though, they have this burger station available everyday, they are something not to miss when you visit! They have like 4 different bread options to choose from, three types of cheeses, and a vegetarian option. I love mine on Pretzel Bread and topped with pepper jack cheese!<br>Another tip for my fellow Yelpers lucky enough to dine at this private paradise is...LEAVE ROOM FOR DESSERT!  It&#39;s almost overwhelming how many options they provide every day. From cheese cake and apple crumb cake, to freshly baked/prepared cookies, pastries, and parfaits! <br>Something to consider as well is, the adjacent cafe &#34;Truck Pit&#34;. Yes, there&#39;s a legitimate food truck that they&#39;ve transplanted to the middle of the 8th Floor cafeteria! You must try the frequently original FroYo flavors that they churn out through the week. Simply addicting and heavenly!<br>Overall, Hemispheres, combined with the Truck Pit, on the 8th Floor of Google&#39;s NYC office location, is hands down one of the best-kept secrets in the Chelsea area!",
