"reviewcomment":"***I wanted to preface this with saying that the location is directly down the street from the 33rd St 7 Train stop. Literally on the first block, on the right hand side, after you cross the West bound side of Queens Boulevard. ***<br><br>Sweet &amp; Sara has long been one of my favorite vegan indulgences. I ordered a bunch of goodies online for my boyfriend for Halloween (hello, Halloween-themed bats and ghosts!) and went to pick them up. I set my appointment for Wednesday on Monday morning but had an opening in my schedule to pick them up earlier, which they happily arranged for. That was really sweet of them.<br><br>Then I got there, and everyone was so nice! I&#39;ve come to the factory before and met Sara and didn&#39;t expect anything but sweetness. It&#39;s a family affair here, folks. Makes me want to start a family business. They were so pleasant and funny. Added bonus: Everything there smells like marshmallows.<br><br>As if it isn&#39;t clear, I love the product, admire the people, and love it when I have time to pick them up at the factory instead of grabbing some from Duane Reade*. <br><br>*Who else is super excited they can get these delicious bits of heaven at the city&#39;s most common drug store? Between the number of Starbucks and Duane Reades per block, I can now pick up marshmallows for the hot cocoa I get down the street at Starbucks. :)",
