"reviewcomment":"Raffetto&#39;s is elysium, and not just because Matt Damon probably drops in occasionally.<br>If you are in some way opposed to Raffetto&#39;s, you are an enemy of pleasure. Used a Google Offer here (Free 1lb of fresh cut noodles when you purchase 1 box of fresh ravioli*) from the charming staff and couldn&#39;t have been happier with my choices, the chestnut fresh pasta emerging from the gnarly guillotine machine and frozen pumpkin ravioli ($6.50 total*, cash only**). Even the website of this since-1906 institution is elegant. Men out there: embrace the iconic bag; I was lucky it&#39;s holiday-colored because it downplayed some of the amused looks I still received brandishing it around.<br><br>**This is the only place I can think of where I support that policy &#39;cause I wholeheartedly endorse the operation lasting, and at a supremely reasonable price point.",
