"reviewcomment":"If you are adventurous with your palate, this small little butcher shop in Carol Gardens might be one of the best things you could come across.  Besides the usual meats you find at a butcher shop, you could walk away with many exotic game meat that you could surprise your unsuspecting loved ones or guests with when they come over for dinner or BBQ.<br><br>I could imagine the scenerio now:<br><br>&#34;Oh, yes indeed honey bun, I made this dish myself. I&#39;m glad you loved it. And here I was a little worried that the phyton snake filet was going to be too tough. Wait.... honey.... why are you making that sound and running to the bathroom so fast for?&#34;<br><br>Yes indeed. They carry phyton snake filets here. Along with such meats as llama patties, camel patties, caribou, alligators filets, and whole snakes.<br><br>They make the standard game meats like bison, buffalo, ostrich, rabbit, frog, and antelope tame by comparison. Which they also carry by the way.<br><br>If your palate is higher end, they have aged steak with differing weeks of aging.  They also carry Japanese Kobe&#39;s slightly cheaper alternative,  American Wagyu. Sadly, they don&#39;t sell real kobe from Japan or Australian Wagyu though.  <br><br>With such a broad range of products, this is a butcher shop for almost everyone&#39;s taste bud, no matter what it is.",
