"reviewcomment":"Visited on a Sunday afternoon. It was packed. &#34;New Harlem&#34; type of crowd.  <br><br>The weather was pretty warm outside, so I got the iced tea. Yum. It was a lemony, red colored tea. Perfectly sweetened. Next time I&#39;ll have to choose my favorite sweetener, honey. <br><br>I grabbed a seat at the long table by the window. Ended up staying for about 1.5 hrs to get some work done on my laptop. Chatted up with some folks at my table. Friendly crowd. <br><br>My iced tea came in a long glass chute personally delivered to me by a waiter. Payment is made at the end, not when you order. I was expecting my bill to come to $7. Nope. My yummy iced tea was only $3.50. Pleasantly surprised. Had to tip.  <br><br>What could improve the experience:<br>-Get a menu board instead of the weird pamphlet thing with the menu <br>-Collect payment at the register. Makes things easier. Less formal. <br>-Maybe display your Balthazar goodies on the counter so people remember to order some. Yum!<br>-I found out about this place on Yelp. From the street, it&#39;s kind of hard to tell that there&#39;s an awesome tea place inside. Find some sensible way to draw attention to your storefront. <br>-Simplify your wifi info. <br><br>New fave tea/coffee place in the nabe.",
