"reviewcomment":"I can&#39;t say enough good things about this place. The food is delicious and fresh. The prices are unbelievable, given the quality and size. I usually get the #3 large combo sub with the marinated mushrooms- SO GOOD. Their sausage bread and cinnamon bread are also pretty great. I often pick up a loaf of one (or both, since they&#39;re so cheap- $2/whole cinnamon bread loaf or whole sausage bread loaf for $4) to bring to friends in central NJ when I visit. The shop is very small and doesn&#39;t have an eat-in section. Around lunch time, this can be very busy. The couple that owns this place is incredibly sweet, and it&#39;s always nice to see them when I stop in for a sandwich. The mozzarella here is very good as well. Just remember- cash only, and it closes early- around 3PM, so you have to get here early. I used to live around the corner from here, so it was an easy trip I&#39;d make at least twice a week. Now that I live closer to Monmouth Deli.....I still find myself stuck on Second Street Bakery.<br><br>Also- something I noticed under the Yelp filtered reviews- a lot that I read under the filtered section that had been removed, actually seemed like legitimate reviews. This place is just that great. I&#39;d probably create a Yelp account just to review and recommend this place.",
