"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Amazing.  I LOVE chocolate (fine, all sweets, but esp. chocolate).  In a city filled with so many delicious options from chocolatiers and chocolate confectioners local and otherwise, this is easily one of my top picks for gift giving.  The NAMA chocolates are incredibly unique and unlike any other chocolate I&#39;ve ever had before.  When I first read about them I was intrigued - so many great reviews and yet I had never heard of them (what?!)..  So obviously the next day I went to the store to check it out.  After trying the samples, I purchased 3 boxes.  A few days later I was back to buy 2 more boxes.  I simply had to share this new finding with my family and closest chocolate loving friends!  Needless to say, they were hooked, too.  I think I probably purchased around 8-10 boxes within a month of first discovering them.<br><br>So what are they?  Well, if you love that creamy, melt-in-your mouth feeling - these are a must.  They&#39;re semi-soft chocolate squares that have to be kept refrigerated. Imagine a cream/fudge/icecream/chocolate orgy.  That&#39;s what NAMA chocolates remind me of.  They do have a &#34;dark chocolate&#34; one but it&#39;s still rather creamy and not so bitter.  Of course, you can ask for a sample and decide for yourself!  The white and matcha ones are yummy, too, but (for me) not as delicious as the milk varieties.  **PAY ATTENTION TO THE EXPIRATION DATE ON THE BACK**.  In my opinion, they taste exponentially better when they are fresher - so plan accordingly to buy AND consume within a few days.  Also - look before you buy and buy the ones with the expiration date that is furthest.  <br><br>Service?  Wonderful.  Every time I have been there the employees have been incredibly sweet (no pun intended) and very happy to help and give out samples.  The packaging is very neat/clean and they will give you an icepack or two depending on the temperature outside and how long it will be before you can get them to a refrigerator.  Plus, free giftwrap upon request!<br><br>I can&#39;t say much as to their other treats.  The chocolate covered potato chips were surprisingly yummy, but I really think the NAMA chocolates steal the show.  I haven&#39;t tried their other chocolate items - I mean, when that money can go towards another box of NAMA chocolates...",
