"reviewcomment":"I Love Staubitz... Ok, thats my review. ..<br><br>Sigh... okok I get to write more than that. <br><br>I&#39;ve been comin to this place since i was a lil kid &amp; before the McFadden family took over.<br><br>Nothing but the best...no - the B-E-S-T! <br><br>Prime Meats (of course) - cheese &amp; bread selection - (for a wedding photo shoot; I had the limo driver stop here for pate, bread &amp; cheese!) - condiments, rubs, sauces, jams, advice! :)<br><br>Over the past 5 years or so, I&#39;ve cut down on my meat considerably... <br>Then one of my old friends tells me he&#39;s getting married &amp; moving to the UK  &amp; another who&#39;s err single now, tells me he misses my cookin...<br>I ended up spending about $200 on fresh meats -vacuum sealed to cook up a Feast! <br>Yep! Nothin but the BEST!<br><br>Yeah, Ive been to that new place on Atlantic nr Trader Joe&#39;s - lets just say they didn&#39;t get my order right. (3 Organic Cornish Hens) <br>Yeah, I&#39;ve been to that place on Smith St - I liked em better before they expanded &amp; the brothers took care of you personally. I asked for fresh organic chicken prepared a certain way (was visiting friends out on the Island) the guy gave it to me Frozen &amp; whole. <br><br>Yeah, ya pay a lil more at Staubitz...<br>I&#39;m happy to pay for the level of service and quality the McFaddens &amp; their crew provide!<br><br>Check &#39;em out! :)",
