"reviewcomment":"This is a bodega. Unremarkable at first glance, but inside lies some of the most unexpectedly delicious Mexican cuisine around. You might not be observant enough to pick up on all the little clues, but I read some Encyclopedia Brown books as a kid, and I saw them all: <br><br>The huge bin of jalapeños off to the side. <br>The bunch of fresh cilantro slung over the counter. <br>The menu of Mexican food. <br>The glowing Yelp reviews about their excellent Mexican food. <br><br>I&#39;m not sure what, but something told me I would enjoy their tacos. And I do. I also love their carnitas torta. Piled high with juicy pork, it was a very, very good sandwich on its own. With a ladleful of the homemade hot sauce they keep behind the counter? It was perfection. <br><br>Oh, and perfection in the South Slope costs only $7, with a bottle of Poland Spring.",
