"reviewcomment":"Came here on a rainy day looking for a cup of coffee. What I found here instead wasn&#39;t the normal kinds of coffee, but rather an interesting menu of Hispanic influenced drinks. Their beans are from Stumptown, but unfortunately it seems like they&#39;ve stopped selling the beans because of lack of demand.  <br><br>I chose to go with what looked like their best seller, the café con leche. The café con leche is much more than the Spanish translation, coffee with milk. It&#39;s creamy and foamy with a pinch of butter and salt, which makes it sound kind of gross, but it&#39;s actually quite wonderful! I had a sip of my friend&#39;s Cuban espresso, and it was also really good. The consistency of the drink was creamy and it had a sweet, smoky taste. <br><br>They serve you at a window, but there&#39;s seating inside and outside. I will definitely be coming back to try the other drinks on the menu.",
