"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"This meat market makes a huge variety of fresh and smoked meats in Polish and German styles. <br><br>From smoked mysliwska, wiejska and weselna to whole smoked chickens, salmon, whitefish, hams, and bacons this place has it all.<br><br>I buy smoked Salmon heads here for cream of salmon soup and Japanese style rice balls, all of the sausages for epic summertime barbeques, cured hams for Christmas gifts, bacon for anything that calls for it, many of the cold cuts and mustards for monster sandwiches, and the homemade pickles.<br><br>If ever you wondered what headcheese was this is the place to try it, they probably have fifteen varieties. All delicious.<br><br>Everything here is inexpensive and of the highest quality.<br><br>My main barrier to entry is that everything is written in Polish and the employees are mainly native Polish speakers. I only know how to say &#34;thank you&#34; and &#34;good morning&#34; in Polish so I do a lot of pointing.<br><br>Best advice. Buy something you don&#39;t recognize each time you go here, then go home and search the web for how to prepare it.<br><br>Or just get as much double smoked mysliwska as you can carry, a jar of spicy mustard, and turn off the phone.",
