"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ll start by saying that I can&#39;t remember ever having a cream puff so maybe my opinion isn&#39;t the best BUT I am a &#34;foodie&#34; and I know good food when I eat it.<br>With that being said, last week at work my regional manager mentioned Beard Papa and she raved about it. She was surprised when I said I&#39;d never been despite growing up in that &#39;hood and babysitting over there also. I wasn&#39;t expecting much honestly. She mentioned that if I&#39;d planned on taking some home for my family I should at least get one big one for myself. <br>Today as a &#34;pre snow&#34; snack I decided to make to short trip. When I walked in I was greeted by a lovely smell. I was literally in heaven from the start. I immediately noticed that today they only had Vanilla and Chocolate filling so for the minis I got both and for my regular sized I got vanilla. The staff was nice and answered my questions. I also got a coffee (it&#39;s MUD). My coffee was tasty but I saved the treats for when I got home. My brother tasted his first and he was instantly obsessed. Because he couldn&#39;t stop talking about it so I tasted mine. I died, was revived and died again off of that heavenly taste. I honestly don&#39;t know how anyone could give this place a bad review. Inexpensive, delicious and a friendly enough staff - sometimes finding all 3 in New York is hard. <br>Thank you Beard Papa, I will be back far more than I probably should!",
