"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/K5DJRBt0mAEUf148wuQOPA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"We ran across Top Hops on accident even though it was on my list of places to try to hit while we were visiting NYC from California.  WOW!  I&#39;m glad we did.  I LOVE this place.  I love it so much we keep talking about maybe needing to open one here at home!   <br><br>The ambiance is cool and beercentric, you have a bar and then cases of beer for sale in bottles, cans, kegs, or fill a growler!  Not many places around here that have those multiple services except for maybe that actual breweries that are serving THEIR beers.  But, these beers are from all over the world.<br><br>At the bar, there is a selection of beers on tap and while we were there Bell&#39;s had just gotten to town so there were a lot of Bell&#39;s beers on tap.  You have an opportunity to do four tasters or purchase a pint.  We did both!  What I realllly loved was the snacks for sale!  An amazing cheese selection and delicious olives- they locally source the cheeses, meats, breads, etc.  LOVE THAT.  <br><br>Enjoyed chatting with the bartender, who seemed knowledgeable about the beers he was serving.  <br><br>I definitely recommend Top Hops if you&#39;re looking for a great place to drink beer and try some new beers.  Just note that there ins&#39;t a lot of seating, so if it&#39;s crowded, it will be a standing situation.",
