"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/dz0sF4DAPuD6Z01cfQM3yQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"As a start-up publisher, fiction editor, and freelance writer, coffee shops and I have a long and complicated relationship. I love supporting local coffee shops, but I also have crippling social anxiety over mispronouncing menu items. I have googled how to pronounce varieties of wine under the table at dinner, and I have walked out of snobby coffee shops when I&#39;m befuddled by the menu. I usually end up banishing my inner coffee critic and holing up at Sbux, mostly because they don&#39;t complain much if I get lost in edits and hang around for an hour. Or more. Let&#39;s be honest. <br><br>I had some critiques to finish before a fiction workshop this morning, so I walked into Birch. So glad I did! Friendly employees who weren&#39;t the least bit West Village Chic (it&#39;s like lemon juice has permeated the water supply), an amazing cappucino, and they didn&#39;t run for the hills when they saw me pull out a laptop. I&#39;ll only stay for half an hour y&#39;all, don&#39;t worry. <br><br>New Saturday morning tradition! I might come by after workshop for some grilled cheese and tomato soup.",
