"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Coffee Foundry is the best. A couple friends and I met up here for the first time a couple months ago to just catch up over coffee and do some work. It&#39;s very cozy and quiet, as most people are usually working on laptops or doing reading, etc. You can sit at the bar, or on tables lined up by the wall. There are also private rooms for karaoke, but the bartender/coffee maker/AWESOME person will let you study in the room if you need more space. We timidly asked if we could possibly pay to use the room for a few hours, and he got it cleaned up for us and said we could have it as long as we needed for free (unless a horde of karaoke-goers came all at once....spoiler: they won&#39;t). So we went back, and did the same thing the next week. <br><br>so you have the best service, great coffee in glasses and mugs (none o dat plastic/paper cup business) for a good price, and yummy treats that he is very good at convincing you to try. (those little mint cupcakes doe) <br><br>love coffee foundry! should be everyone&#39;s go-to work spot. (but not really because that would suck for us.)",
