"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QGG7-0zlx4T9L4rQBNcr2g/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"It&#39;s a good thing The Dead Rabbit is all but in the middle of nowhere, otherwise there&#39;d be no way anyone could ever experience one of the best new cocktail bars in New York City.<br><br>&#34;Middle of nowhere&#34; might be a little dramatic, but really - it&#39;s hard to get to. The Financial District all but clears out once the Wolves of Wall Street have gone home, and the closest train is the 1 that ends its route at the Staten Island Ferry terminal. Not exactly the sort of spot you just stumble upon - when you end up here, it was by no accident. I guess the R is pretty close too, but still - it&#39;s in the boonies, so to speak. <br><br>I tend to shy away from the typical Irish bar settings because I think they&#39;re lame and lazy. Throw some Guinness on tap, add a few bros wearing green shirts, and boom - you have a bar. But Dead Rabbit reinvents the Irish bar in a way that all others of its ilk should replicate. It&#39;s got that warm, broken in feel though it&#39;s only been operating for the better part of a year, their menu extends way beyond the usual fried pub grub, and their mixed drinks are second to none. Throw in an impressive scotch and whiskey list, three floors with a different vibe at each one, and you have yourself a tier 1 destination for alcoholic indulgence.",
