"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Shaikh&#39;s Place / Donut Shoppe. How I love thee. Let me count the ways.<br><br>1. Their donuts are INCREDIBLE. Freshly baked all the time. Never stale. Cheaper than Dunkin Donuts. Their chocolate glazed are my favorite. <br><br>2. They&#39;ve got tacos. I don&#39;t know how many types of tacos, and I&#39;ve always stuck to chicken. But their chicken/ tomato/ onion/ cilantro tacos that come with a lime wedge, and salsa roja + salsa verde = HEAVEN! And for $2! Can&#39;t go wrong. I don&#39;t think they have any sour cream, but when I asked for &#34;white sauce&#34; (akin to the St. James white sauce in Astoria) they gave me, when seemed to be, something along the lines of Miracle Whip. No bother, though. <br><br>3. They&#39;ve got delicious melt-in-your mouth pancakes. 3 huge ones for $4!<br><br>4. They&#39;re open 24/7. That&#39;s right - 24/7 - so if it&#39;s 3am, and you&#39;re oddly like me, and craving a late-night pancakes, tacos &amp; donut fix (that happens *far* more often than it should) - then you&#39;ve found the perfect spot.<br><br>I hear they have other items offered aside from the 3 listed above, but I&#39;ve never seen an actual menu - whether in-store, or for take-out, so I&#39;m not sure. <br><br>But man, you&#39;re really missing out if you&#39;ve never been here! I love you Shaikh&#39;s Place / Donut Shoppe!",
