"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"In the immortal words of poet D&#39;Mite, &#34;Your body needs water, so drink that shit&#34; and likewise &#34;Read a book! Read a book! Read a muh&#39;fuckin book&#34; but not just any book, get one from Bluestockings.  Social justice themed books? Yes. Books covering topics like race, class, and the environment, in addition to fiction and poetry? Oh yes, yes. Nothing censored here. You&#39;d likely have to special order most titles at larger bookstores, if they even dared to carry or obtain them.  <br><br>Bluestockings is volunteer and donation supported which helps them host many interesting free events. They also have a cafe serving fair-trade coffee and vegan baked goods. <br><br>According to their website they carry over 6000 titles on topics such as queer and gender studies, global capitalism, feminism, police and prisons, democracy studies, and black liberation. <br><br>I&#39;ve been to free readings here. The place is cozy and quaint for it and depending on the night, you might listen real people reading experiences from the heart making you a better human for it. Your mileage may vary but mine was great.",
