"reviewcomment":"The absolute best and filling breakfast sandwich I have ever had in NYC.  Granted, it&#39;s my first and only breakfast bagel sandwich I have ever had in NYC, nonetheless, I was fully satisfied.  <br><br>My friend had an itchin&#39; for a deluxe smoked salmon bagel sandwich so she suggested we grab deluxe bagel sandwiches before we went shopping.  We yelped different bagel shops near our hotel and the closest one was Best Bagel and Coffee.  <br><br>When we got there, I was surprised by how small the shop was.  There&#39;s about four seats facing the window, but realistically only three people can fit sitting down, and two other tables. I ordered the bacon, egg, and cheese with a coffee.  <br><br>The bagel sandwiches were huge...<br>I could only finish half.  It wasn&#39;t greasy and the eggs didn&#39;t taste fake like most bagel places make them.  The bagels themselves definitely lived up to the NYC bagel hype.  They were fresh, moist, thick, and of course, huge.  The coffee was extremely delicious and fresh as well.  My friend could not stop raving on about it.  I was too busy gulping it down to say anything. <br><br>A huge bagel sandwich and a hot fresh of coffee for under $5 is money very well spent!",
