"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_Cr27mlJjpa5t1IppLRt8A/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"When I first moved to New York, I knew nothing about the restaurants in my neighborhood. My mother would constantly bring me to this cafe, which was right across the street from our apartment. <br><br>For breakfast, lunch, and dinner, my brothers and I would order something different from here. We were poor, and the food proportions were huge as well as very cheap. The Hong Kong milk tea, span macaroni, and pork chop over rice are to die for.<br><br>When we moved to Brooklyn, the one thing I missed most about Manhattan was S.Wan Cafe. I had 3 free swipes on my metrocard provided by my high school. One was used in the morning to get to school, one was used to stop by S.Wan Cafe to pick something up, and the last was used to go to Brooklyn, happily clutching my food.<br><br>Some may find this routine tedious but I love the food so much that it was worth it.<br><br>I have since gone to a college upstate. For my fall break, Thanksgiving break, and winter break, I always made sure to stop by S.Wan Cafe no matter where I ended up staying.<br><br>Today is my last day in New York City for awhile. Needless to say, I am sitting in S.Wan Cafe at this very moment, enjoying my perfect Hong Kong Milk Tea and spam macaroni. <br><br>Until we meet again, S.Wan.",
