"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/TcU1aweDiw-u9u2WbtwlDg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Simply put, Addeo&#39;s is one of the finest bread bakeries in NYC.  On par with places like Il Fornaretto and Royal Crown in Brooklyn.  Caputo&#39;s on Court, which one reviewer below mentioned, is good but overrated based on location; if you disagree, then stick to cozy little Carroll Gardens and leave places like Addeo&#39;s to the people with taste buds.<br><br>They own this shop, as well as a store front on Arthur Ave.  I recommend coming to this location instead, as it&#39;s the original and they typically are better stocked.  While they offer all kinds of different varieties and shapes of breads, I just go with an Italian baguette with sesame seeds.  Crisp and crusty on the outside and moist and soft on the inside with awesome fresh flavor, it&#39;s what Italian bread is supposed to be.  Their bread sticks are also great.  Its all good enough that I try to go only to restaurants nearby that stock their bread!<br><br>If you&#39;re on Arthur Avenue, this is a must visit.  If you&#39;re not on Arthur Avenue, get your ass up here so you can get some of this!",
