"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/eQJdJgxZIV9rrLGktQ8NUQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I actually took a wines class in college (it was one of the most popular classes for credit and everything!) but I sadly and unfortunately don&#39;t remember much other than the major wine regions and varietals (&#34;But shouldn&#39;t you know this stuff?&#34; says everyone). So, I was more than relieved when I walked into Sutton Wine Shop and was greeted and guided towards the perfect bottle for a dinner at a BYO restaurant. <br><br>I asked for a medium-bodied, preferably French red that would work well with poultry and pork. With a twinkle in his eye, the staff member (I should have asked for his name!) led me to the Pinot Noir section and went on a very easy-to-understand spiel about the sorts of wines he recommended, as well as some personal stories. He also actually pushed for wines in the $15 to $25 range, and said that there really was no reason to spend money when a perfectly wonderful wine could be purchased for cheaper. <br><br>They have a wide selection of wines and a smaller selection of other spirits. There&#39;s a whole shelf near the entrance that features wines that are &#34;buy 1 get one 50% off&#34;. They make deliveries within NYC and will even gift wrap. Online shopping is also available on their website, but the warm helpfulness of the staff is something worth coming in for. <br><br>There&#39;s a 10% off check-in offer! <br><br>Likelihood of another visit:<br>&#34;Have a nice dinner! Come back and let us know what you thought!&#34; <br>Will do.<br>They also have weekly wine tastings!",
