"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"It&#39;s a shame I found one of my favorite yogurt shops I&#39;ve come across so far in all of NY, and it&#39;s way out in Staten Island.<br><br>True to it&#39;s location in a little mini-mall in Staten Island, this place doesn&#39;t have all of that flash and the bright colors and funkiness you see at other places like 16 Handles. The yogurt speaks for itself here - they have 14 flavors, with several of the great sweet ones on rotation at most of the chains (peanut butter, red velvet, cake batter, cheesecake, etc.), and they all tasted awesome. I know, because the sweet old guy running the place gave us a bunch of sample cups and just told us to help ourselves.<br><br>Aside from the great tasting yogurt and the most important sample factor, the other aspect of a self-serve shop, the toppings, was on point. They had several different kinds of crushed nuts, as well as all of the chopped candy bars and other stuff you can think of that they should have.<br><br>As mentioned above, the guy working the register was super nice too, and made some very pleasant conversation while I weighed my tub of yogurt.<br><br>If I ever set foot on the island again, I&#39;m definitely coming here for a really satisfying, refreshing, lighter dessert.",
