"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ll be honest, when Vanilla Sky first opened a while back, I was resistant to liking it. I had been frequenting a different fro-yo place on 30th ave (no, not 16 handles) and felt some sort of loyalty, as well as preferred their lower price per ounce. <br><br>Over the summer I had a project I was working on outside of work and decided to just go to this closer frozen place than walk the three avenues in surface of the sun heat to my other place on 30th Ave. Not to mention they finally had coconut yogurt, which they didn&#39;t when I first tried them out after opening (anyone who knows me knows my coconut fixation). <br><br>I grabbed my delicious cooling treat, tossed in a few fresh fruit choices (kiwis, strawberries, and blackberries FTW!), and maybe one or two gummy bears, and parked myself in the back to hammer away at my project. <br><br>The atmosphere in the back is great, but only when there are no screaming children. It can echo back there is all I&#39;m saying. Anyway, plenty of comfy seats, plugs, and free wifi make this a great place to get stuff done. <br><br>Oh! And they make AMAZING coffee!! I&#39;ve had a hot latte and an iced coffee and loved both!  <br><br>Vanilla Sky converted me over the summer of &#39;13. They can rest assured I&#39;m a regular!",
