"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/yS5wY8Aioo5XtS7kNuZP1w/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"If you just want to indulge on the finer things in life, preferably in croissant form, then come right in!<br><br>They bake their breads &amp; pastries fresh daily in store; the almond croissant has to be my personal favorite. It&#39;s super soft, with the perfect flaky outside with sliced almonds. I could seriously have three of these. (You can split one in half if you&#39;d like, but I suggest you just eat it all...it&#39;s hard to share)<br><br>The baguettes are super good when warmed up to perfection, having the cheese melt and fuse with the ham... omg. The Mango-Kiwi mini cakes give a nice boost of sweetness without going overboard. (So if you&#39;re diabetic, you&#39;ll be okay with one)<br><br>The napoleon...I could have everyday. It&#39;s so flaky, so fresh, so wow. Much yum.<br><br>Everything in here is great, really. I can&#39;t pick which is better. (The almond croissant. It beats everything.)<br><br>The line can get pretty long on Fridays &amp; Saturdays, especially during the morning. But it&#39;s worth the wait &amp; they attend pretty quickly. You can have a seat somewhere &amp; chat away if you&#39;d like. But if you stay too long, you might just buy everything there &amp; become obese.<br><br>...but that&#39;s okay, right?<br>I mean, those almond croissants will make you happy..<br>Very happy.",
