"reviewcomment":"Most of the staff are well informed and willing to spend time explaining your potential purchase<br><br>The store itself is beautiful which makes for a happy shopping experience and the wine available is 5 Star<br><br>Prices are generally fair though occasionally slightly (I&#39;m talking slight, like 50cents maybe a dollar) more than other stores  or online (believe me I checked) - what makes me not mind this though is that the wines are kept in wine happy environments (no wine stupidly stored above a blasting heater) so your purchase is always delicious <br><br>Why not 5 Stars??<br><br>Most of the wines are more than $15-20 before tax, and even though they have a entire long table devoted to $10 wines I&#39;ve tried them all (don&#39;t judge!!)... and can&#39;t say I love any of them.  <br><br>So, when I&#39;m looking for a reasonably good bottle to share with my sweets on a Tuesday night I head to Roebling wine and Liquor.  When I want something guaranteed delicious to pair with some pan seared sea scallops I&#39;m heading to DOC.<br><br>Did I mention they deliver, for free?? And it&#39;s fast?  I&#39;ve talked myself back to 5 stars, more like 4.8 but I&#39;m rounding up, because I want them to stick around, and they&#39;re overall awesome.",
