"reviewcomment":"You know know you&#39;re an obsessive when you travel to a whole other borough on the off chance that a hole in the wall liquor store carries the booze you&#39;re looking for.  That is how I ended up at Whiskey Shop:  I have an addiction to the brown stuff and I&#39;ll travel cross-country if need be (or cross-borough, same thing).<br><br>I&#39;d like to think that I&#39;ve loved bourbon before it was cool (possible not true) back when there were few varieties to be had and places weren&#39;t selling 2 oz pours for $175 (no exaggeration).  That said, the recent uptick in bourbon obsession has definitely expanded the genre for the better, that realization coming during my chat with the gentleman behind the counter (whom I presume is Jonathan?) over the pros and cons of various mashbills and distilling styles.<br><br>I probably soured our discussion when I mentioned the allocation of the rare stuff.  His eyes kind of glazed over and he went into a robotic recitation of their policies.  However, that didn&#39;t stop me from walking out with a great craft whiskey in my hands and a smile on my face.",
