"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been looking for a good place to buy quality suds since moving to the city from the beer loving Pacific Northwest, and I&#39;ve definitely found that place in Malt &amp; Mold.  My favorite thing about this place is the growlers, which you can fill from any of the taps which are always rotating with beer from local breweries and breweries around the country.  Also, in addition to the standard 64 oz growler and the half size 32 oz, they have 16.5 oz growlers (real flip top growlers, not silly mason jars).  These are great if, like me, you&#39;d rather try a small amount of a variety of beers than get a whole bunch of one thing.  The selection of bottled beer is awesome as well, with a lot of hard to find things in stock.<br>They also have a ton of high quality cheese, meat, bread, and the like.  Unfortunately artisanal cheese doesn&#39;t fit in my grad student budget, but it all looks wonderful.<br>And of course, the owner Kevin is helpful, knowledgable, and takes a genuine interest in his customers.<br>Definitely worth the regular trip from Harlem!",
