"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I am not so much a food truck guy, but what I am is an italian style sandwich guy. I first saw Diso&#39;s while walking around midtown looking for a lunch spot. I never give up an oppurtunity to try an italian style sandwich, and needless to say, I couldnt be more happy that I stumbled upon this gem of a food spot.<br><br>This was a long time ago, when Diso&#39;s was still working out the kinks. I have been going back to them every week, trying different things on the menu. I have yet to be disappointed. The quality of the bread, meats, veggies, and spreads are truly the freshest I have had in the city. Diso&#39;s continues to satisfy.<br><br>You truly get that neighborhood vibe waiting for your sandwich. The guys in the back are always talkative and happy to bust your chops. It is all around an experience you will seldom find outside the classic Italian neighborhoods.<br><br>This is the first (and probably only) review I will ever write, but Diso&#39;s is that worth it. There has not been a single trip here that I have been disappointed. and all this from a food truck! All said and done, Diso&#39;s deserves every bit of success coming their way. Bravo guys!",
