"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/FtxSUecG4iopQIC8GgW-IQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This is the best tasting Blue Bottle location in NYC but my least favorite to get to, as it is hidden in an office building basement. I first discovered Blue Bottle in San Francisco and I can assure you this is about as close as you can get to the taste you get there. The baristas here really, really know what they are doing and the shots they pull are virtually the best I have had in NYC.<br><br>So yeah, this place is really small and intense and really hard to get to, but I promise the shots pulled here are MUCH better than the other NYC Blue Bottle locations. The espresso here is acidic, with a deep crema and an almost smoky bite. But that is Blue Bottle and, for me, that is heaven.<br><br>If you make the hike to bowels of Rock Center plaza (it is down the center lobby stairs and then down a hall to the left, by Wichcraft) make sure to get the Parmesan Shortbread. Oh my, this Parmesan Shortbread. I would happily eat myself to oblivion with this stuff if I could somehow get it near my apartment. <br><br>Anyway, I wish this wasn&#39;t the tastiest Blue Bottle outpost (because it definitely isn&#39;t the easiest to get to) but unfortunately it is. So, good luck and bring your compass!",
