"reviewcomment":"Many years ago, I lived in Prague, where the cold winter walks would often lead me to Cafe Louvre to seek the restorative powers of their magical hot chocolate. Two shots of the stuff would leave me delirious with a theobromine high. I&#39;ve missed that hot chocolate enough to recreate it at home. At long last, I can say that I&#39;ve found a place that is nearly its equal in Mariebelle.<br><br>To be clear, I could ignore the rest of the food offerings: the attraction here is the cakes and the hot chocolate.<br><br>The hot chocolate you want is the one made with water(!), European Style. It is not dissimilar from drinking half a melted chocolate bar, slightly diluted (which is how I make it at home). You can feel the warm thick liquid as it goes down and makes everything right with the world (temporary effect).<br><br>Who cares that it also happens to be in a be in a beautiful space or that you are practically sitting on your neighbor&#39;s lap? Nothing matters but the chocolate!",
