"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I did not want to go to People&#39;s Pops. I really, really did not want to.<br><br>Why?<br><br>I knew it was going to be absurdly delicious. People&#39;s Pop would also be the last thing I would eat before leaving New York.<br><br>I did not want this foodie vacation to end. But everything must come to an end, and if I was going to do it right, I would end my incredible trip with a refreshing People&#39;s Pops popsicle.<br><br>We made our way over to the People&#39;s Pops stand, and I decided to get a chai fig popsicle while my friend decided to get the red plum basil popsicle. <br><br>We sat down on the bench in front of Van Leeuwen&#39;s and started unwrapping our pops. I took a slow bite from my chai fig popsicle and... wow. Every bite had a bit of fresh fig accompanied by the subtle but fragrant chai that I&#39;ve always loved. So we sat there, swinging our feet and gnawing on our popsicles as dogs and humans walked by, staring at us strangely as we constantly &#34;mmmmm&#39;ed&#34; with every bite.<br><br>I couldn&#39;t have ended my trip on a better dessert. It was a humid day, I didn&#39;t have very much money left and all I wanted was something cold and refreshing, and People&#39;s Pops had it. Now if only they would set up shop in LA....",
