"reviewcomment":"As my fiance and I plan for our honeymoon, the only request I have for our stay in Italy (forget sightseeing) is to treat ourselves to local gelato after every meal (yes, breakfast too). <br><br>After spending much of my free time lately in East village (coffee shop, cafe hopping), Fresco&#39;s whimsical chalkboard sign finally convinced me to stop in one freezing afternoon for a very weather appropriate treat. <br><br>I have returned multiple times since (even took one my best girlfriends for a post brunch date sweet run). I loved every flavors they have to offer - peach yogurt, a la mode, ferrero, ginger snap, chiquita, biscotti - just the few that I&#39;ve tried and can&#39;t get enough so far! <br><br>In addition, they are extremely generous (the 1 scoop is HUGE), so patient (sample as many flavors as you want), and they allow you to mix your 1 scoop with 2 flavors! For just $4, I get my 1 giant scoop in a waffle cone - so satisfying! (they are currently offering $5 paypal offer - on my first visit, my cone was free!)<br><br>Will definitely return to try the other flavors - heard about the goat milk ice cream - ah can&#39;t wait for it to return for the season!",
