"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"One of the only Italian bakeries left in Sunset Park. <br><br>When you walk in, you are greeted by a lovely old Italian grandma who says, &#34;GOOD MORNING.&#34; <br>When I ask her what&#39;s good, she says, &#34;EVERYTHING.&#34; <br><br>Like the service, the pastries are sweet, but not overly sweet. Since discovering this bakery in the midst of Mexican restaurants of Sunset Park, I can tell it is very special. It delivers all you could want from a bakery like Veniero&#39;s, but it doesn&#39;t have the hype surrounded it. This keeps the prices low and our bellies full. After selecting a series of cakes, I must say I cannot choose a favorite. The strawberry shortcake was very rich, almost like a wedding cake. The strawberry jelly enhanced the flavor of the butter cream just a bit. The tiramisu was perfumed with liquor and had traces of salt and other spices. The chocolate mousse was light and airy and full of flavor. The cookies are fresh and delicious. This Italian family definitely knows what they are doing and have been doing it for years.",
