"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"It&#39;s big, it&#39;s organized, it&#39;s always stocked heavily and it&#39;s right up the street from my crib.  Therefore, this is my go-to liquor store.  If you&#39;re in the immediate area and want some funky cold medina, this is the place you need to go to.  There really isn&#39;t anything you can&#39;t find here.<br><br>The owners are extremely chill and are very amicable.  If you need assistance, they will be more than willing to help.  After coming in one night to grab a bottle of Ciroc Coconut for a house party, one of the owners, in his heavy accent asks, &#34;Why you buy that for? Because of the P Diddy?&#34;  He directed me to a cheaper coconut vodka called Pearl.  It was a good call.  There&#39;s a vast array of whatever your favorite poison is.  If you walk in on the right Friday night, you might even get lucky with a complimentary tasting of whatever new brand is on the scene.<br><br>However, I do most of my wine purchasing here.  Not for anything super fancy.  Just standard table wine to have in the crib when I&#39;m chilling or having dinner with my girlfriend.  They also carry my favorite prosecco, Mionetto (look for the big orange label).  It&#39;s perpetually in stock.  We use that instead of regular champagne for mimosas.  I&#39;ve been known to wipe the place clean of these bottles when I have brunch w/ friends at my apartment.<br><br>I&#39;ll gladly continue to give L &amp; P my money as long as my liver will allow me.  My only issue with the place is that I also play my Lotto here and I haven&#39;t won yet.",
