"reviewcomment":"I celebrated my birthday at Bosie Tea Parlor with several girl friends (+2 boys)! Bosie is an absolutely darling tea parlor nestled in the west village, and we all traipsed in dressed in our summer dresses (on a cold winter afternoon) for the occasion. <br><br>I ordered the Bosie Tea Service for 2, which comes with the following per person:<br><br>- 2-cup pot of tea (includes most teas on the menu)<br>- 2 mini scones with clotted cream and jam<br>- 3 portions of tea sandwiches<br>- 2 mini tea cakes<br>- Choice of two macarons<br><br>When you order tea service for 2, the food comes out on this adorable 3-tiered serving platter.  It might not sound like a lot of food but my boyfriend and I were actually stuffed by the end. <br><br>The cucumber sandwiches were yummy, along with my jasmine and rose macarons. I just love how delicate and dainty tea sandwiches look. The tea cakes were dense and moist, with green tea being my favorite. Since I usually order savory items for brunch, the sweet pastries became a little overwhelming towards the end.<br><br>Tea service is a bit on the expensive side ($29 for one, $55 for two), but very comparable to other tea parlors I&#39;ve been to in the city like Lady Mendl&#39;s Tea Saloon. If you&#39;re not in the mood for tea they also have a great brunch menu. I tried a friend&#39;s lorraine quiche - absolutely delicious! If I come back I&#39;m definitely trying the brunch menu.",
