"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/LCyl7_CY9OTJBQLD4kWZlg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"My boyfriend suggested this place after a misfortunate lunch at a unnamed Filipino restaurant down the street. He had been coming here for years with his family to get dessert after dinner. He did not disappoint. <br><br>Now this was what I&#39;m talking about when a mom and pop shop do it right! The whole place smelled of deliciously fresh baked pan de sal. When you step into the bakery you are greeted with lines, shelves and racks of Filipino pastries and breads, it&#39;s quite a beautiful sight to look at. <br><br>I will say get there early, cause the good stuff goes fast. This place was quite picked through when we got there, but it&#39;s ok cause it was the Sunday before Christmas. I know everybody was buying up the house for the holidays. <br><br>They also serve food in the back the portions are large, cost a little more than some Filipino restaurants down the road but it looked pretty good. Especially the half fried fish. All of the dishes are lovingly served on real plates which gives that nice home feeling and the tables and chairs in the back are nice and large, much like our diner table back home. <br><br>This place has been in business for more than 20 years and I can see why. Can&#39;t wait for the next visit!",
