"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/A82jkKvQ177a-jiX059dRQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"A real fish market!<br><br>This doesn&#39;t seem to publicize themselves as super gourmet, but the stuff here is obviously fresh and awesome! They have a huge selection of whole fish on ice, some really nice-looking fillets, and pieces of larger fish that they will cut for you into steaks. There&#39;s also some nice looking shellfish staples (mussels, shrimp, multiple kinds of scallops, oysters, lobsters, etc), although this isn&#39;t the kind of place that has 10 types of gourmet oysters. Staff are very attentive and will clean or fillet or do any kind of processing for you on the whole fish you select. I didn&#39;t look carefully, but there also freezer cases with really large packages of things like crab legs, etc. The prices overall are EXCELLENT, and the quality was great. We came home and cooked our bag of mussels and whole fish that night - not a single mussel had to be thrown out because it was cracked or had died (usually the supermarket bags are half dead and open!), and the fish was delicious and didn&#39;t have a trace of the &#34;fishiness&#34; that comes from unfresh seafood.<br><br>All in all, a great go-to fish market for your regular seafood needs!",
