"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QktZXnQu_lYLP53LSRmXeg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This is a godsend for Ft. Greene / Clinton Hill. Flavorful, super rich-tasting coffee made anyway you like it (10,000 or so brewing methods? yes please!). It is indeed some of the best coffee in NY or perhaps the universe, although I think every roaster and shop has a special thing going for itself that makes it hard to call any one of them the best (Toby&#39;s Estate for their pour overs, Cafe Grumpy with the Chemex, Blue Bottle for their New Orleans Iced Coffee, Joe Pro Shop in the city for their guest espresso, etc.). But even if you don&#39;t live in the hood, WTF is worth the trek, especially for their pour overs, siphons, and my personal favorite: the sock pot (I don&#39;t know of anywhere else in the city that uses this brewing method). It brings out so many flavors!<br><br>Great staff, too-- it&#39;s got that small-town feeling where they&#39;ll get to know your name and the way you like your order every time. Love it.",
