"reviewcomment":"UPDATE on 11/18 -- owner addressed shipping information in message below; dry ice provided. Thanks!<br><br>I had my food delivered to New Jersey. It came via UPS in a little more than 24 hours. The temperature outside was running in the upper 50s for the week. The contents of my box were cold, but pretty much thawed. <br><br>Being familiar with vegan food, I wasn&#39;t alarmed because I&#39;m&#39; not dealing with animal flesh, eggs and dairy in the products, so I knew there was nothing to be worried about. Though, I was a little surprised there was no ice pack or dry ice for the $26 shipping cost. <br><br>I had to spend at least $50 before I could have the items delivered, so I got all different products to try. (I&#39;ll edit my review as I try more, but so far the food is excellent). The chicken nuggets are tasty and have a real meaty texture, though, I wouldn&#39;t order it again. There&#39;s absolutely nothing wrong with these nuggets; they&#39;re just not my cup of tea. The citrus ribs are excellent; the soy protein is in small pieces and covered in a sweet, tangy, savory sauce. I&#39;m excited to try the drumsticks (which are featured on a youtube video with the Vegan Zombie -- love him! -- watch the video and you can see how he cooks it).<br><br>The soy-free chicken fried steak is great. I gave it a good pan fry and served it with stuffing and gravy.<br><br>If you are familiar with the Veggie Heaven restaurants in New Jersey (Teaneck, Montclair, and Denville) -- these vegan products from May-Wah taste just like those, so I think these restaurants must order from them. I love Veggie Heaven, so I&#39;m happy to have found this market. I researched May-Wah via feedback from their customers on Facebook and on general Internet sites. It&#39;s a solid, safe company in business for decades. I&#39;m so happy to have found them. I can&#39;t wait to try the vegan lobster!",
