"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/a8qzb3fx4NOdQZCKMaJrZQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been living in Crown Heights for about 4 months now (but making weekly visits for the past year whilst living in Carroll Gardens), and Little Zelda is, without question, my favorite coffee shop in the neighborhood. I say this based on the quality of coffee/pastries, the friendly-ness of baristas, and the overall ambience. <br><br>Coffee: Their drip coffee is Toby&#39;s Estate, so obviously it&#39;s going to be great. Their cold brew is on point (a cold brew is NOT just drip coffee that&#39;s put in the refrigerator). Their espresso-based drinks are made with care; their mocha (I prefer it over ice) is my mocha-of-choice in all of Brooklyn. <br><br>Pastries: All their pastries are delectable - though there&#39;s not much I can really say except for you should give them a shot. The cheddar and chive biscuit is their most popular item; personally, I cannot get enough of the apple turnovers warmed-up. Flakey crust on the outside, thick apple sauce (chunky, not TOO sweet) on the inside. They&#39;re sold out half the time so you&#39;ll have a better shot at one in the morning. They also have a wide selection of gourmet pop-tarts. <br><br>Baristas: Some of the friendliest people in the neighborhood. <br><br>Ambience: Though I mention this last, the ambience is ultimately what earns Little Zelda a 5-star rating. Their round tables are just far enough apart that you can sit down (with a friend) comfortably, yet close enough that you can jump into your neighbors conversations (not in a creepy way please). There&#39;s always appropriate music in the background, and the lights dim in the evenings. The decor is accentuated by the tastefully placed antiques. Seriously, take a look around at all the little things. <br><br>Spend some time here, thank me later.",
