"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/g08ssg3c4vdvj-acsr7V7Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I came in here looking for something for a potluck dinner once and I&#39;m really glad I did. Everyone on yelp talks about the currant rolls and the coconut bread, which I&#39;m sure are good, but one thing keeps me coming back here: the guava turnovers. I love turnovers and usually you can only get the ones with apple filling. If you haven&#39;t had a turnover before it is like the calzone version of an apple pie. A triangle of puff pastry with fruit inside. Combine that with a delicious guava filling and you have the perfect pastry. This is the only place I&#39;ve seen that has the guava flavor, but they also have pineapple and the traditional apple. The first time I went they only had one left so it&#39;s a popular item. Get there early or go on a weekday!<br><br>Also, when I went this kid (maybe 10) was sent to get bread at Allan&#39;s by his mom and he got pretty confused about how much bread he was supposed to buy. The people at Allan&#39;s were really sweet about it and helped the kid out. I like a store that takes the time to help all their customers even when there is a line.",
