"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/jQ0owonMla39gxX1JpGx7A/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"OK, they&#39;re among the Coffee Elite in Manhattan. This is established. They&#39;re not a roaster, but they always have top notch beans. Given that, the pastries are from Blue Sky Bakery, and amazing. I never in my life expected to be excited about muffins, but try them. You&#39;ll understand. And be warned: the afternoon cookies are larger than they appear. I struggled to finish one.<br><br>This is also my go to when buying my own beans. They&#39;re always fresh, within a few weeks of the roasting date, and seem to cycle them out before they&#39;re past a month from roasting (give or take). After buying them, and stowing them in my bag during work, I can smell them through the bag, and end up craving another cup all day. They&#39;re so fresh and wonderful.<br><br>I also like going here to get some work done on a day off, although the counter space is tight. Be warned: the wrong time of day, the line can be out the door.",
