"reviewcomment":"Dear Amy,<br><br>Thank you for providing me with the utmost delicious foods/treats that always manage to perk up my day. I like that you have three locations around NYC, so I know that I don&#39;t have to travel too far to get my sweet tooth fix. Your shop is quaint, classic and has that home-y feeling. I know that I can always look forward to the highest of quality products at your store.<br><br>As for your breads... hearty, crusty, chewy and (using the European method) shaped by hand. I must admit, I could probably eat a loaf by myself. But I won&#39;t. I can always expect a good variety since you make over 20 different loaves a day. All carefully handled with love and care.<br><br>And we cannot forgot about the desserts and pastries. Your cupcakes were moist and flavorful. So far I&#39;ve tried: carrot, red velvet and vanilla -- all delightful. The muffins (Zucchini Carrot Apple Walnut &amp; Blueberry) brought me on a trip down memory lane. And that Pain Au Chocolat... heavenly. <br><br>So what I&#39;m trying to say is thank you Amy. Your food brings smiles to many faces and adds inches to many people&#39;s waistlines. (Hey you gotta take the bitter with the sweet!)<br><br>Sincerely,<br>Katie",
